
grep "error" app.log = basis seearch

grep -i "error" app.log = case insensitive search

grep -n "error" app.log = show the number of lines

grep -r "error" app.log = search recursively inside a directory

grep -v "INFO" app.log = show only lines that don't match

grep -c "exception" app.log = count how manu times a pattern appear onlog

Real-time error monitoring:
  tail -f applicaiotn.log | grep -i exception
during debugging 
